title: I support Sorsha, TBH, and Durianrider got it right on this one.
description: As Stannis Baratheon said, a good deed does not wash out the bad: I can't believe we've got vegans pretending that it's a valid argument to say, "Yeah, well, I donate money to charity, THEREFORE…"  Please.  I don't care if you donate to charity, and I don't care if you own the charity: that doesn't dispose of the basic premise of ethical veganism, and, in fact, it's completely spurious to everything Sorsha had to say.
